30.02	Jon_Meacham	Jon Meacham	Jon Meacham (born May 20, 1969) is executive editor and executive vice president at Random House. A former editor of Newsweek and a Pulitzer Prize winning bestselling author and a commentator on politics, history, and religious faith in America, he is a contributing editor to Time magazine and editor-at-large of WNET Public Media, the New York public television station.	
